The paper discusses the Text Encoding Initiative (TEI), which is a standard for encoding digital documents, particularly in the humanities. This makes cs.DL (Digital Libraries) the most likely category, as it deals with the organization and management of digital documents. The paper also discusses issues related to the use of TEI in digital document projects, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the technical framework of TEI, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
